   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Agentic Research Assistant\\n\",\"**NLP Project 94 of 100** — Search, retrieve, summarize, then self-check answers using a multi-step agent.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['numpy','sentence-transformers','scikit-learn','requests']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, requests, re\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\nfrom sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nmodel = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Knowledge base\\nDOCS = [\\n    'Python was created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.',\\n    'TensorFlow is an open-source ML framework developed by Google Brain team.',\\n    'BERT was introduced by Google in 2018 as a bidirectional transformer model.',\\n    'GPT models use autoregressive generation trained on large text corpora.',\\n    'RAG combines retrieval with generation for grounded answers.',\\n    'Transformers use self-attention mechanisms to process sequences in parallel.',\\n    'Fine-tuning adapts a pre-trained model to a specific downstream task.',\\n    'RLHF aligns language models with human preferences using reward models.',\\n]\\n\\ndoc_embs = model.encode(DOCS)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Agent Pipeline: Search → Summarize → Self-Check\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def agent_answer(question):\\n    print(f'\\\\n🔍 Question: {question}')\\n    \\n    # Step 1: Retrieve\\n    q_emb = model.encode([question])\\n    sims = cosine_similarity(q_emb, doc_embs)[0]\\n    top_idx = sims.argsort()[-3:][::-1]\\n    context = [DOCS[i] for i in top_idx]\\n    print(f'📄 Retrieved {len(context)} docs (top sim: {sims[top_idx[0]]:.3f})')\\n    \\n    # Step 2: Generate answer\\n    context_str = '\\\\n'.join(context)\\n    prompt = f'Answer the question using only the context. Be concise.\\\\nContext:\\\\n{context_str}\\\\nQuestion: {question} /no_think'\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':'qwen3:1.7b','prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        answer = r.json().get('response', context_str)\\n    except:\\n        answer = context[0]  # Fallback to top retrieved doc\\n    print(f'💬 Answer: {answer[:200]}')\\n    \\n    # Step 3: Self-check (verify answer against context)\\n    answer_emb = model.encode([answer])\\n    support_score = cosine_similarity(answer_emb, model.encode(context)).max()\\n    grounded = support_score > 0.3\\n    print(f'✅ Grounded: {grounded} (support score: {support_score:.3f})')\\n    \\n    return {'answer': answer, 'grounded': grounded, 'support_score': round(support_score, 3)}\\n\\nquestions = ['What is BERT?', 'How does RAG work?', 'Who created Python?']\\nfor q in questions:\\n    agent_answer(q)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Agentic architecture: retrieve → generate → verify** ensures answer quality.\\n\",\"- **Self-checking catches hallucinated or unsupported answers.**\\n\",\"- **For production, add iterative retrieval** (re-query if confidence is low).\\n\",\"- **This pattern is the foundation** of modern RAG agents.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
